[Name]  SDL_sound
[Summary]  Sound Sample Library for SDL (Simple DirectMedia Layer)
[Description]  SDL_sound is a library that handles the decoding of several popular sound file formats, such as wav, ogg mp3 and midi. SDL_sound can just play a file or alternatively decode a file and hand back a single pointer to the waveform. SDL_sound also can handle channel conversion on-the-fly and behind-the-scenes.
[Suse Category]  System/Libraries
[License]  LGPL
[Homepage]  http://icculus.org/SDL_sound/
